{"lemma":"قُرْبانُ","slug":"قُرْبانُ","root":"ق.ر.ب","root_slug":"ق-ر-ب","root_link":"/words/roots/ق-ر-ب","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun_prop","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":true,"lemma_key":"قُرْبان","root":"قرب","pos":"N","occurrence_count":3},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":2,"pos_tags":["noun"],"has_etymology":true,"sense_count":4},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n35400","n35401"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D9%82%D9%8F%D8%B1%D9%92%D8%A8%D8%A7%D9%86%D9%8F"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"noun","gloss":"sacrifice to God, gift to God, corban"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"sacrificial animal, victim"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"Eucharist, Holy Communion"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"verbal noun of قَرِبَ (qariba) (form I)","tags":["form-of","noun-from-verb"]}]},"etymology":{"source":"wiktextract","text":"Etymology tree\nAramaic קורבנא (qurbānā)bor.\nArabic قربان\nBorrowed from Aramaic קורבנא (qurbānā). Compare Hebrew קָרְבָּן (qorbān)."},"ipa":["/qur.baːn/","/ɡur.baːn/","[ɡʊr.baːn]","/qir.baːn/"],"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n35400","headword_ar":"قَرْبَانُ","root":"qrb","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"A vessel"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"nearly full:"},{"kind":"text","text":"fem."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qurobaY","text_ar":"قُرْبَى"},{"kind":"text","text":": (S, O, K:) and pl."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qiraAbN","text_ar":"قِرَابٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (S, O:) you say"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qadaHN qarobaAnu","text_ar":"قَدَحٌ قَرْبَانُ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maA='F","text_ar":"مَا=ءً"},{"kind":"text","text":"i. e. ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A drinking vessel"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"nearly full of water:"},{"kind":"text","text":"and the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"q","text_ar":"ق"},{"kind":"text","text":"in"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qrbAn","text_ar":"قربان"},{"kind":"text","text":"is [said to be] sometimes changed into"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"k","text_ar":"ك"},{"kind":"text","text":": (TA:) so accord. to Yaakoob; but ISd denies this. (TA in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"krb","text_ar":"كرب"},{"kind":"text","text":".)       -A2-  See also the paragraph here following."}],"source_refs":["S","O","K","TA"]},{"entry_id":"n35401","headword_ar":"قُرْبَانٌ","root":"qrb","body":[{"kind":"text","text":": see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qurobapN","text_ar":"قُرْبَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": [it may often be rendered"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"An offering,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"oblation:"},{"kind":"text","text":"and hence it sometimes means"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a sacrifice,"},{"kind":"text","text":"as in the Kur iii. 179:] pl."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qaraAbiynu","text_ar":"قَرَابِينُ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (Msb.)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qurobaAnuhumo dimaA=w^uhumo","text_ar":"قُرْبَانُهُمْ دِمَا=وُهُمْ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Their offering"},{"kind":"text","text":"to God"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"is their blood,"},{"kind":"text","text":"lit."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"bloods,"},{"kind":"text","text":"] occurs in a trad. as cited from the Book of the Law revealed to Moses, and as referring to the Arabs; meaning, they seek to bring themselves near unto God by shedding their blood in fighting in the cause of religion; whereas the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qrbAn","text_ar":"قربان"},{"kind":"text","text":"of preceding peoples consisted in the slaughtering of oxen or cows, and sheep or goats, and camels. (TA.) And it is said in another trad.,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlS~alaApu qurobaAnu kul~i","text_ar":"الصَّلَاةُ قُرْبَانُ كُلِّ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"taqiY~K","text_ar":"تَقِىٍّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The divinely-appointed act of prayer is the offering"},{"kind":"text","text":"to God"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of every pious person"},{"kind":"text","text":"]; meaning, that whereby the pious seek to bring themselves near unto God. (TA.) ―         -b2-  Also, (S, A, O, K,) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qarobaAnN","text_ar":"قَرْبَانٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (K,) but this latter is by some disapproved, (TA,) ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A near associate;"},{"kind":"text","text":"or]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a particular,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"special,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(A, K,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"associate"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"companion"},{"kind":"text","text":"(A) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"consessor;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K;) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a consessor;"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a particular,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"special, associate"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"companion;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, ISd, O;) [or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a familiar,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"favourite;"},{"kind":"text","text":"] of a king, (S, ISd, A, O, K,) or of a governor, or prince; (S, O;) [or of any person who is either a superior or an equal;] so called because of his nearness: (TA:) pl."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qaraAbiynu","text_ar":"قَرَابِينُ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (S, A, O, K:) and one says also,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fulaAnN mino qurobaAni AlA^amiyri","text_ar":"فُلَانٌ مِنْ قُرْبَانِ الاَمِيرِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Such a one is of the near associates,"},{"kind":"text","text":"&c.,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of the governor,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"prince"},{"kind":"text","text":"]; (S, O;) [for]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qurobaAnN","text_ar":"قُرْبَانٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is [said to be originally] an inf. n., and [therefore, as an epithet,] the same as sing. and dual and pl.: (so in a marginal note in one of my copies of the S:) or, in a phrase of this kind, it is a pl. of ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qariybN","text_ar":"قَرِيبٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":". (A in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bEd","text_ar":"بعد"},{"kind":"text","text":".)"}],"source_refs":["S","A","O","K","TA","ISd"]}]}}